Abdomen. Abdominal terga (
Fig. 17
) and sterna translucent, eXcept terga VIII–X white. Terga III–VII with a pair of orange brown stripes on each side; tergum V with thin stripes; tergum IX with round brownish maculae medially. Cerci colourless.

Genitalia colourless (
Fig. 19
), with 3-segmented gonopods, limit between first and second segments barely visible. Unistyliger with a pointed apophysis at apeX of inner margin; first segment stout, without setae; second segment with subparallel margins widened apically; third segment short, oval.
